## Steps
- Observation
- Preliminary research
	- Do some poking around to see if there's already a satisfactory explanation
	- If there isn't one, or it isn't tested enough, you should find out for yourself!
- Hypothesis
	- Any testable observation of a phenomenon that can be supported or rejected by tests
	- Can become a theory when
		- Supported by an abundance of evidence
		- Passed many tests and failed none
- Design an experiment
- Perform the experiment
- Analyze results
- Draw conclusions
	- Based on measurable/observable evidence
	- Science is self-correcting: new evidence may lead to reconsideration of ideas previously believed to be fact after undergoing rigorous testing
- Summarize the whole process
- Peer Review
	- When publishing, work can be rejected, or have revisions requested before acceptance
- Consider further question




- ## Hypothesis vs theory


| Hypothesis                   | Theory                                         |
| ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Testable                     | Tested                                         |
| Can be supported or rejected | Has been supported by an abundance of evidence |
|                              | Passed many tests, failed none                 |
